1
00:00:00,644 --> 00:00:05,644
CUAS-DETECT. Counter-UAS RF detection for Marine installation force protection.

2
00:00:05,648 --> 00:00:10,648
LOGCOM Installation Incident Response. The OOD has thirty seconds to call it.

3
00:00:10,652 --> 00:00:16,652
Six sample spectrograms — DJI Mavic, Parrot Anafi, fixed-wing, hobbyist quad, swarm, ambient.

4
00:00:16,691 --> 00:00:23,691
Stage 1: heuristic features. Numpy on the spectrogram — peak bins, hop period, modulation hint.

5
00:00:23,699 --> 00:00:29,699
Stage 2: multimodal AI engine ingests the spectrogram. Structured CUAS JSON.

6
00:00:29,701 --> 00:00:35,701
Class, controller signature, intent, range, recommended COA, EOC callout.

7
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:41,600
Operator picks the swarm capture. Pipeline reruns end-to-end.

8
00:00:41,604 --> 00:00:46,604
Stage 3: hero model writes the CUAS Engagement Recommendation.

9
00:00:46,605 --> 00:00:52,605
BLUF, contact ID, threat assessment, ROE-graded options, recommended COA.

10
00:00:52,607 --> 00:00:58,607
Engagement options graded passive, non-kinetic, kinetic — each with required authority.

11
00:00:58,617 --> 00:01:03,617
Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL — same code, now on the Inference Mesh.

12
00:01:03,618 --> 00:01:08,618
IL5 / IL6 ready. ReBAC. Air-gapped. Zero data movement.

13
00:01:08,619 --> 00:01:13,619
CUAS-DETECT. Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Powered by Kamiwaza.
